## 📂 Directory Layout

```txt
{{projectName}}/
├── docs/                      # AI-ready documentation (this folder)
{{#eq frontendFramework "Next.js"}}
├── src/
│   ├── app/                   # Next.js App Router (pages, layouts, route handlers)
│   ├── components/            # Reusable UI component library (atoms, molecules)
│   ├── hooks/                 # Custom React hooks
│   ├── lib/                   # Config configurations (database clients, auth SDKs)
│   └── types/                 # Custom type declarations
{{else if (eq frontendFramework "React + Vite")}}
├── src/
│   ├── components/            # Reusable UI components
│   ├── hooks/                 # Custom React hooks
│   ├── pages/                 # Page layouts and route views
│   ├── store/                 # State management ({{stateManagement}})
│   ├── utils/                 # General helpers and formatting scripts
│   ├── main.tsx               # Client entry point
│   └── App.tsx                # Main App Shell
{{else}}
├── src/                       # Main source directory
{{#eq backend "Express"}}
│   ├── controllers/           # Route handler controllers
│   ├── middleware/            # Express request middleware
│   ├── routes/                # Endpoint routing definitions
│   ├── services/              # Business operations logic
│   └── app.ts                 # Express entry point
{{else if (eq backend "FastAPI")}}
│   ├── app/                   # FastAPI application package
│   │   ├── api/               # Route routers by domain
│   │   ├── models/            # SQLAlchemy / ORM models
│   │   ├── schemas/           # Pydantic request/response schemas
│   │   ├── core/              # Config, security, dependencies
│   │   ├── db/                # Database session management
│   │   └── main.py            # FastAPI entry point
│   ├── tests/                 # Pytest test suite
│   ├── requirements.txt       # Python dependency manifest
│   └── pyproject.toml         # Project metadata (optional)
{{else if (eq backend "NestJS")}}
│   ├── modules/               # Domain feature modules
│   ├── common/                # Shared decorators and guards
│   ├── main.ts                # NestJS launch entrypoint
│   └── app.module.ts          # Core root module
{{/eq}}
{{/eq}}
├── tests/                     # Test suite specs ({{testingFramework}})
├── package.json               # Package setup and dependencies
└── tsconfig.json              # TypeScript compilation rules
```

---

## 🔍 Folder Contexts

### `docs/`
Contains architectural documents, glossary terms, and instructions for developers and AI agents. Keep files up to date when changing APIs or rules.

{{#ne frontendFramework "None"}}
### `src/components/`
Every component should be self-contained in a folder, containing the markup, layout styling, and standard documentation (e.g. `components/Button/Button.tsx`).
{{/ne}}

{{#ne backend "None"}}
### Service Boundary
Ensure backend/server logic is isolated from frontend components. Backend queries, database connections, and private API keys should only be invoked within server environments.
{{/ne}}

